{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Madhuri et al. [88] found that up to 30% zeolite replacement reduces pore size and connectivity, improving impermeability.",
    "Tran et al. [90] observed that zeolite refines pore structure, lowering total porosity and increasing resistance to sulfate and chloride.",
    "Samimi et al. [91] reported that a 10% zeolite replacement reduces micro-cracks and voids, strengthening the interfacial transition zone (ITZ) and enhancing bonding and permeability.",
    "Malolepszy et al. [89] confirmed that zeolite decreases porosity and average pore size, leading to better resistance against sulfate and acid attacks.",
    "Jokar et al. [92] found a 12-15% reduction in water absorption with zeolite due to its micro-filling effect."
  ],
